{{ 'dev-fibre-benefits.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
{%- comment -%} No JS: the Brief's Interactivity section is "none" — 3 static cards. {%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%} Fixed design tokens from Figma — not merchant-controlled {%- endcomment -%}
<style>
  .fibre-benefits {
    --font-body: 'Public Sans', sans-serif;
    --font-heading: 'Test Tiempos Headline', serif;

    /* Full-bleed by design. No --container-max: Brief note #1 — the content row is w-full,
       there is no centred max-width frame in this node (same precedent as dev-trust-badges
       and dev-site-header). The only horizontal inset is --section-px. */
    --section-px: 64px;
    --section-px-mobile: 16px;

    /* Mobile artboard specifies its own top spacer (48px), not a scale factor off desktop. */
    --pt-mobile: 48px;

    --font-heading-size: 20px;
    --font-heading-weight: 500;
    --font-heading-lh: 1.2;
    --font-body-size: 16px;
    --font-body-size-mobile: 14px;
    --font-body-weight: 500;
    --font-body-lh: 1.4;

    --spacing-sm: 4px;  /* heading -> body */
    --spacing-md: 16px; /* card padding; icon -> text block (desktop); card -> card (mobile) */
    --spacing-lg: 24px; /* card -> card (desktop); cream-container padding */

    /* Measured off the Figma artboards, not guessed:
       mobile cards 1 & 2 use a flat 4px gap between every child, card 3 uses 8px between the
       icon and its heading+body sub-group. Brief note #3 — a real authoring inconsistency in
       the source file, built as measured rather than silently normalised.
       (Card-3 mobile height checks out to the pixel only with 8px: 16+48+8+24+4+40+16 = 156.) */
    --card-icon-gap-mobile: 4px;
    --card-icon-gap-mobile-alt: 8px;

    /* Layout slot for the icon. Fixed 48x48 on BOTH artboards. */
    --icon-size: 48px;

    /* Confirmed from the exported artwork itself: every path is #666666 (Neutral/500).
       Drives currentColor on the two inline icons. */
    --icon-color: #666666;

    /* Render size == viewBox, so each icon draws at its true Figma size. Verified against the
       375 artboard at 1:1 (no scaling): the ink bounding boxes measure 46x48 / 43x44 / 48x50.
       The Brief's "Images" table is the Figma ANCHOR box and understates biodegradable — its
       art is 50px tall and deliberately overflows the 48px slot by 1px top and bottom. Sizing
       to the anchor box would letterbox and shrink the art. */
    --icon-no-chemicals-w: 46px;
    --icon-no-chemicals-h: 48px;
    --icon-fsc-certified-w: 43px;
    --icon-fsc-certified-h: 44px;
    --icon-biodegradable-w: 48px;
    --icon-biodegradable-h: 50px;
  }
</style>

<div
  class="fibre-benefits"
  style="
    --bg: {{ section.settings.background_color }};
    --page-bg: {{ section.settings.page_background_color }};
    --card-bg: {{ section.settings.card_background_color }};
    --color: {{ section.settings.text_color }};
    --accent: {{ section.settings.accent_color }};
    --pt: {{ section.settings.padding_top }}px;
    --pb: {{ section.settings.padding_bottom }}px;
    --card-radius: {{ section.settings.card_radius }}px;
    --container-radius: {{ section.settings.container_radius }}px;
  "
>
  {%- comment -%}
    Two nested background layers, exactly as authored (Brief note #2):
    the root carries the PAGE background and the top spacer; __inner is the cream band.
    Verified against both artboards — the 80px desktop spacer and the 48px mobile spacer are
    page-cream (#FFFCF4), NOT band-cream (#FCF5E3); the band starts below them. On mobile the
    band becomes a 32px-rounded card inset by a 16px gutter; on desktop it is full-bleed and
    square. Same element, two skins — no CSS trick, a real wrapper with its own 24px padding.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="fibre-benefits__inner">
    {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
      {%- liquid
        assign icon_key = block.settings.icon
        assign icon_mod = block.settings.icon | replace: '_', '-'
        assign icon_uid = section.id | append: '-' | append: forloop.index
      -%}
      <article class="fibre-benefits__card fibre-benefits__card--{{ icon_mod }}" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
        <div class="fibre-benefits__icon fibre-benefits__icon--{{ icon_mod }}">
          {%- if block.settings.icon_image != blank -%}
            {%- liquid
              assign icon_alt = block.settings.icon_image.alt | default: '' | escape
              assign icon_src = block.settings.icon_image | image_url: width: 144
            -%}
            {{
              icon_src
              | image_tag:
                loading: 'lazy',
                widths: '48, 96, 144',
                sizes: '48px',
                alt: icon_alt,
                class: 'fibre-benefits__icon-img'
            }}
          {%- elsif icon_key == 'no_chemicals' -%}
